==English==

===Etymology===
Latin [[approximatus]], [[p.p.]] of [[approximare]] to approach; ad + [[proximare]] to come near.  See  [[Proximate]].

===Pronunciation===
; adjective : IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈpɹɑks.ə.mɪt/
*{{audio|en-us-approximate-adj.ogg|Audio (US)}}
; verb : IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈpɹɑks.ə.maɪt/
*{{audio|en-us-approximate-verb.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''approximate'''
# [[approaching|Approaching]]; [[proximate]]; nearly [[resembling]].
# Near [[correctness]]; nearly [[exact]]; not perfectly [[accurate]].
#: '''''Approximate''' results or values.''

====Related terms====
*[[approximately]]

====Quotations====
<blockquote>
To help carry out its mission, NASA's Genesis spacecraft has on board
an ion monitor to record the speed, density, temperature and approximate 
composition of the solar wind ions.
</blockquote>

